---
interface Props {
  active: "employers" | "programs";
  employerCount: number;
  programCount: number;
}
const { active, employerCount, programCount } = Astro.props;
---

<header class="topbar">
  <div class="brand">
    <span class="brand-mark">AD</span>
    <span>
      <span class="brand-name">Audio Directory</span><br />
      <span class="brand-sub">Jobs &amp; grad programs</span>
    </span>
  </div>

  <nav class="tabs" aria-label="Directory sections">
    <a class="tab" href="/" aria-current={active === "employers" ? "page" : undefined}>
      Employers <span class="count">{employerCount}</span>
    </a>
    <a class="tab" href="/programs" aria-current={active === "programs" ? "page" : undefined}>
      Programs <span class="count">{programCount}</span>
    </a>
  </nav>
  <div class="topbar-actions">
    <button class="help-trigger" type="button" data-help-open aria-haspopup="dialog" aria-controls="help-title">
      ? <span>How to read this</span>
    </button>
  </div>
</header>

<aside class="detail help" data-help-panel hidden>
  <div class="detail-scrim" data-help-close></div>
  <div class="detail-card help-card" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="help-title" tabindex="-1">
    <div class="detail-head">
      <div class="detail-titles">
        <h2 id="help-title">How to read this</h2>
        <span class="help-sub">What the sectors, entry paths, minors, and grad links are telling you.</span>
      </div>
      <button class="detail-x" type="button" data-help-close aria-label="Close help" title="Close">×</button>
    </div>
    <div class="detail-body help-body">
      <div class="field">
        <dt>Sectors</dt>
        <dd>
          A sector is a lane in audio work, like games, post-production, acoustics, or immersive audio. Employers can sit in more than one lane.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <dt>Entry paths</dt>
        <dd>
          The badge in <b>Getting in</b> is a quick signal about how reachable that lane usually is right after undergrad.
        </dd>
        <ul class="help-list">
          <li><b>Open to new grads</b>: direct junior or early-career paths are common.</li>
          <li><b>Experience first</b>: internships, assisting, or adjacent work usually comes before stronger roles.</li>
          <li><b>Grad school recommended</b>: extra specialization often helps materially, but is not always mandatory.</li>
          <li><b>Grad school required</b>: the field often expects graduate credentials or equivalent specialist training.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <dt>Bridging the gap</dt>
        <dd>
          Suggested minors show which DSU add-ons can make you more credible in a field. Grad-path links jump to relevant programs when a sector usually rewards deeper specialization.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>
